# Rasm Core

Rasm is a RhinoWIP macOS monorepo targeting `.NET 10`, C# 14, GH2, Eto, and app-bundle host assemblies from `/Applications/RhinoWIP.app`.

## Required reads (in order)

1. `CLAUDE.md` — manifest, dependency policy, universal constraints, quality gates, file sections
2. Root `AGENTS.md` — navigation, language policy, documentation policy, live Rhino bridge
3. Nearest nested `AGENTS.md` for the folder under edit

## Skill routing

Use repo `.claude/skills/` first for Rasm procedures. Fall back to `~/.codex/skills/` only when repo skills do not cover a file type. Do not create Cursor skills.

| File | Skill |
| --- | --- |
| Production `.cs` | `coding-csharp` |
| `.spec.cs`, `.verify.csx`, testkit | `cs-testing` |
| `.sh` | `coding-bash` |
| `.md`, `.mdc` | `docgen` + `style-standards` |
| `.ts`, `.tsx` | `coding-ts` |
| `.py` | `coding-python` |
| `.sql` | `coding-pg` |

## Invariants

- Collapse concept density into existing polymorphic owners before adding files, helpers, wrappers, or shims.
- Keep OOP native boundaries small and singular; keep internals functional with `Fin`, `Validation`, `Eff`, `Option`, folds, and typed errors.
- Treat C# as LanguageExt-first functional ROP; do not import TypeScript Effect patterns into C# rails.
- Treat approved dependencies and local docs as implementation surfaces; do not hand-roll covered behavior.
- Preserve macOS RhinoWIP/GH2 assumptions. Do not import GH1, Rhino 8, Windows, or global-memory guidance.

## Quality Gates

| Rail | Command |
| --- | --- |
| Static C# | `uv run python -m tools.quality static check` |
| Full static, trigger files only | `uv run python -m tools.quality static full` |
| Unit tests | `uv run python -m tools.quality test run [<filter>]` |
| Rhino runtime | `uv run python -m tools.quality bridge verify <scenario-or-glob>` |

`quality static`, focused `--target` test runs, and bridge dotnet routes in `tools.quality` isolate MSBuild scratch under `.artifacts/agents/<pid>/` and may run concurrently. Default `tools.quality test run` (managed `Rasm` target) runs VSTest then Stryker in one invocation — do not parallelize two default test runs. Bridge verify/check/package and live Rhino remain single-flight.

Keep rails orthogonal. Trust `CSP####` analyzer findings and fix architecture rather than suppressing.
